  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting ethics education in Central Asia for sustainable development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO supports Member States in reinforcement of their capacities in the area of ethics education since it becomes an integral part of promoting knowledge-based, sustainable and equitable development. Central Asia is not an exception. The rapidly expanding knowledge in every area of inquiry, and especially in life and biological sciences, is continuously pushing the limits of what people can do. However, ethics education in Central Asia is still undervalued but it is a well-known fact that the quality of ethics education largely depends on the substantive and pedagogic competences of the teacher. An effective ethics teacher should be knowledgeable about how to teach, as well as what to teach to the students.</narrative>
  </description>
